Cool Ideas will slash the price of its uncapped home fibre packages that run on Openserve’s infrastructure, with a promotion from 1 May to 30 September. “We’ve decided to cut our Openserve pricing very aggressively over the next five months to try and get more subscribers on the Openserve network,” said Cool Ideas. Its aim is to get consumers to convert from ADSL to fibre by making it more affordable. Along with significant price reductions, Cool Ideas will offering free installation valued at R1,250, and a complimentary router. “Any customer who signs up from now will also benefit from the special pricing.” All Cool Ideas’ packages are month-to-month and uncapped. Its line bundles and data-only prices are summarised in the table below.